records.addlTxt:
Matter is recalled. Same appearances. Defense withdraws request for PSI and wishes to proceed to sentencing today, 1/7/16 date is removed from the Court's calendar.  Clerk notified probation department re: cancellation of PSI order.  Statements made as to sentencing.  
The Court sentenced the defendant to a MAXIMUM TERM OF IMPRISONMENT of 2 YEARS; the INITIAL TERM OF CONFINEMENT in the Wisconsin State Prison System is 1 YEAR; the MAXIMUM TERM OF EXTENDED SUPERVISION is 1 YEAR. If revoked, all terms and conditions of probation to apply. The defendant is eligible for the Challenge Incarceration Program and is eligible for the "Wisconsin Substance Abuse Program".
The Court STAYED this sentence and placed the defendant on probation for a period of 2 YEARS with the following conditions:  
*serve 90 DAYS in the House of Correction (imposed and stayed); 
*follow through with mental health treatment and take prescribed medications; 
*seek and maintain employment;
*no weapons;
*maintain absolute sobriety; 
*all other terms and conditions deemed appropriate by the probation department. 
Defendant shall provide a DNA sample for the Data Bank and pay all appropriate costs.
Court ordered defendant to pay all applicable court costs and surcharges.
As to all costs and surcharges, amounts to be paid during the period of probation, or if not paid, a civil judgment is ordered. 
Court advised defendant that as a convicted felon he may never possess a firearm or body armor. Court advised defendant that his voting rights are suspended and he may not vote in any election until his civil rights are restored. 

Filed,
Written Explanation of Determinate Sentence;
Notice of Right to Seek Postconviction Relief;
Sentencing submissions of defense.
